    "note": "Super ecliptic pHluorin (Marina's fluorophore, the ArcLight FP) carries the S65T mutation found in EGFP, which collapses its excitation to a single ~488 nm peak — i.e. it is spectrally near-identical to EGFP (the dual-band 395/475 nm spectrum belongs to the older ecliptic pHluorin / epArcLight, not super ecliptic pHluorin). No measured super ecliptic pHluorin ex/em curve is published (FPbase has the protein but no curve data; the ArcLight and Marina papers have no spectrum figure), so the FPbase EGFP excitation/emission curve is used as a near-exact representation (peaks 488/511). Replaces a prior curve that was the EGFP excitation verbatim plus the EGFP emission red-shifted +4 nm (a fabricated shift that mis-placed the emission peak at 515 nm).",
    "proofread": false,
    "source": "FPbase: EGFP",
    "sourceFigure": "FPbase"
  },
